Boil a large #pot{} of salted water for the @dried rigatoni{180%g}.

When boiling, add the rigatoni to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until softened, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pot, off the heat. Drizzle with @oil{to taste} and stir through to prevent sticking.

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{2%units}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced). Halve the @bell pepper{1%unit}(halved and sliced into thin strips) and discard the core and seeds. Halve the @cherry tomatoes{125%g}(halved).

== Pangrattato ==

Place a pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}. When hot, add the @breadcrumbs{1%pack} and half the @harissa spice mix{1%sachet}. Fry until crispy, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. Remove from the pan and set aside.

== Pasta ==

Wipe and return the pan to medium-high heat with another drizzle of @oil{to taste}. Once hot, fry the onion and bell pepper until softened, stirring occasionally, ~{4-5%minutes}. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. Add the cherry tomatoes and cook until softened, another ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add the @passata{1%pack}, @creme fraiche{110%g}, @vegetable stock{1%sachet}, @sugar{1/2%tsp}, @water{50%ml} and remaining harissa spice mix. Cover and simmer for ~{4-5%minutes}.

Stir through the @harissa paste{1%sachet}, @honey{1%sachet} and a knob of @butter{to taste}. Add a splash of water if the sauce is too thick. Mix in the cooked and drained pasta. Season to taste with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and @sugar{to taste}.

> Double the water and sugar amounts for 4p.

Divide the spicy pepper pasta between #bowls{}. Drain and tear the @mozzarella{125%g}, then scatter it over the top. Top with the crunchy flavoured pangrattato.